55, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 659, \"end\": 668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Guy_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9824541369253388, \"rank\": 0.017851239669423005, \"text\": \"James Guy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Guy_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Guy_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 670, \"end\": 678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.999993659336817, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Dean\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 680, \"end\": 693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\", \"score\": 0.8167390230818359, \"rank\": 0.2243767313019458, \"text\": \"Matt Richards\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richards_(footballer,_born_1984)\"}, {\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.5688623505850181, \"rank\": 0.7578945046581913, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There could well be more memorable golds ahead for the Brits on Wednesday, with another busy schedule to come across a whole range of different sporting disciplines.\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 922, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From 7am: Triathlons  Pollution have sufficiently receded in the River Seine and pre-race safety inspections were passed, so both triathlons will take centre stage early on Wednesday morning.\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 1115, \"entities\": [{